            <title>[SOLR-13499] Fix &quot;Apache License, Version 2.0&quot; spelling -- in pom.xml.template </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-13499</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are many Java libraries licensed under &quot;Apache License, Version 2.0&quot; that do not use its official spelling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes issues like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MPIR-382:&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MPIR-382:&lt;/a&gt; with every library defining its own spelling, it&apos;s difficult in large projects to have a clear view of all licenses in use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solr uses &quot;Apache 2&quot; instead of the official &quot;Apache License, Version 2.0&quot; spelling. ...&lt;em&gt;in the pom.xml.template file used by the shadow maven build&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
